qubox — Cline Agent Rules
=========================

IDENTITY
--------
You are working in the qubox repository. qubox is a cQED experiment framework targeting
Quantum Machines hardware (OPX+ + Octave, QUA API v1.2.6). This controls real quantum hardware.
Physical correctness is never optional.

BEFORE EVERY TASK
-----------------
1. Read AGENTS.md completely. It is the master policy document.
2. Follow the Startup Checklist in AGENTS.md §3.
3. Follow the Priority Hierarchy in AGENTS.md §2 when policies conflict.

PYTHON VERSION
--------------
- Required: 3.12.13
- Fallback: 3.11.8 — only on ECE-SHANKAR-07 (hardware access machine)
- Forbidden: all other versions unless user explicitly authorizes
- Style: PEP 8, ruff linter, 120-char line length
- from __future__ import annotations in every module
- Pydantic v2 for data models; frozen dataclasses for identity objects

QUA CODE RULES
--------------
- The compiled QUA program is the source of truth, not the written code.
- Validate every QUA change through the simulator before declaring it done.
- Compilation must complete in under 1 minute.
- Validation shortcuts: n_avg=1, shorten idle periods, simulate minimum duration.
- Hosted server: host="10.157.36.68", cluster_name="Cluster_2". Do not substitute.
- Mismatches between intent and compiled behavior must be reported, never silently accepted.
- Document unresolvable mismatches in limitations/qua_related_limitations.md.

STANDARD EXPERIMENTS
--------------------
- standard_experiments.md defines trust gates for compilation logic.
- If your change touches pulse-sequence generation, compilation, scheduling, or QUA translation:
  verify relevant standard experiments still pass.
- Failure = do not ship without explanation and user approval.

DOCUMENTATION RULES
-------------------
- Every user-visible change updates API_REFERENCE.md and docs/CHANGELOG.md in the same task.
- A notebook that breaks from a code change is incomplete work.
- Changelog is append-only. Never rewrite history.

BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY
----------------------
- Do not rename or remove public APIs without explicit user approval.
- Breaking changes require: API_REFERENCE.md update + docs/CHANGELOG.md entry + notebook updates.

CHANGE SCOPE
------------
- Make the smallest correct change that addresses the task.
- Do not add unrelated cleanup.
- Do not introduce new abstractions without justification from repeated structure.
- Extend existing patterns before creating new ones.

LEGACY CODE
-----------
- qubox_v2_legacy is deprecated. All legacy code now lives in qubox/legacy/.
- Do not add new imports from qubox_v2_legacy. Use qubox.legacy.* instead.
- The notebook import surface is qubox.notebook.

PROMPT LOGGING
--------------
- Log every completed task to: past_prompt/YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS_<task_name>.md
- Use tools/log_prompt.py to generate the file.
- Never overwrite prior logs.

WHAT NOT TO DO
--------------
- Do not silently accept mismatches between intended and compiled behavior.
- Do not rename or remove public APIs without explicit approval.
- Do not assume compatibility with non-QM hardware.
- Do not assume QM API compatibility beyond 1.2.6.
- Do not use Python versions outside 3.12.x or 3.11.x.
- Do not skip docs updates when user-visible behavior changes.
- Do not scatter temp scripts or utilities outside tools/.
- Do not import directly from qubox_v2_legacy.
- Do not introduce new abstractions without justification.
- Do not overwrite prior prompt logs.
